<br>
Overview <br>
<br>
Recent changes to the Skald’s Battlesong line has gone a long way in helping Skalds. Spell failure is down and damage is more consistent over the course of battles. There are still issues with the Skald class as I will outline below, but overall the changes have been positive and well received.<br>
<br>
Concerns <br>
<br>
Battle Shouts – The War Howl (43) and the Battle Howl (44) seem to be reversed. The natural progression of these lines would indicate that they might have been swapped. Currently if a Skald chooses to take their weapon to 50, they are left with a secondary shout that is 2 levels below their current shout. The return for doing this as it is currently set up dissuades a possibly viable spec.<br>
<br>
Resist Chants – Currently we have 6 separate resist chants. While it is group ability, a possible review of them would give the Skalds more to offer their group. As Skalds cannot twist their songs, only one song will ever be playing per Skald. Since that is the case, inefficient songs such as this need to be looked at. Enhancing these will also have the effect of enhancing our group abilities.<br>
<br>
Song Pulses Dropping – A long-standing issue with the Skald class is that we have frequent loss of the pulses of our songs. The speed song will drop pulses, especially when grouped, and will cause all sorts of warping effects and loss of /follow with groupmates. Our DA also skips pulses, and it is typical to see that we have lost 1 or 2 pulses during the course of a single battle. <br>
<br>
Defense – While the recent changes helped our Offense, and the extra HP helped our survivability a bit, we still suffer from low defense. Parry being our only means of defensive speccing does not return enough value to warrant losing offensive ability. This is probably an issue with most classes that have lower defense and the ability to spec Parry as well.<br>
<br>
<br>
Specline Issues<br>
<br>
Weapon – As it currently stands, the return on investment for sacrificing Battlesongs and/of Parry for higher weapon skill is poor. A Skald who specs higher in their weapon line will not offer more damage in exchange for losing offensive shouts and group chants.<br>
<br>
Parry - The only speccable means of defense for the Skald is relegated to getting the leftover Spec points. A typical Skald will end up with a Parry of 17. Since we need to Spec high in Battlesongs and Weapon just to be competitive, we have to use RAs to balance out this spec. Lowering either Battlesong or Weapon does not return worthy results, even with the current changes to Parry/Block. <br>
<br>
New Issues <br>
<br>
With the addition of Trials of Atlantis, the Speed pulse-dropping bug has become even more pronounced. This also created a new issue of mobs popping into existence too late and we are on top of them by the time they are drawn to the screen.<br>
<br>
Other Issues <br>
<br>
Fury of the Gods RA – Please review this unique RA since it is woefully inadequate for its cost.<br>
<br>
Skald Epic Design – Currently it is a slightly redesigned Minstrel Epic graphic. We would like something unique to our class as other classes have.<br>
